I love bread pudding and have made many versions, this is THE BEST! I made it as printed with the following adjustments: added 1/2 cup pecans, doubled the vanilla, doubled the cinnimon, used Grand Marnier to soak raisins & added 3 tsps of the soaking liquid to the egg mixture, had fresh french loaf so sliced it and left the slices on the counter overnight to dry. I baked it on convection and it took 8 minutes less than written. It was HEAVEN!!!!

Rating: 3
OUtstanding recipe, and very easy. I made it largely as written, except for doubling the recipe (perfect for 9x13 pan). I did add about 4 tbs of the bourbon from the raisins to the pudding, and the rest of the bourbon from soaking was the perfect amount for the sauce. Had a little trouble with the sauce separating as it cooled, but didn't have a double boiler, which may have been the problem. Next time would add a pinch of salt to pudding and sauce.

