Rating: 4
This recipe was simply heaven. I used a firm stale baguette and cut it into cubes. Didn't bother to trim the crust. It baked up golden and crisp at the top. The texture was what bread pudding should be smooth and comforting. I didn't have bourbon, so I used rum. Soaked the raisins in the warmed rum for ~30 minutes. Drained the raisins and reserved the rum for the sauce. I was worried about the bread being so hard, but i let it sit in the egg mixture for 30 minutes just to make sure it soaked up the liquid. The bread pudding came out perfectly.

